description.para:
An estimator $\hat{q}$$\hat{q}$ of tail quantiles with level $\alpha$$\alpha$ based on order statistics $X_{1:n} \leq X_{2:n} \leq\dots\leq X_{n:n}$$X_{1:n} \leq X_{2:n} \leq\dots\leq X_{n:n}$ of weighted samples are given by $X_{\lambda:n}$$X_{\lambda:n}$ (left tail) and $X_{\rho:n}$$X_{\rho:n}$ (right tail), where \f[
    \lambda = \inf\left\{ l \left| \frac{1}{\bar{w}_n}\sum_{i=1}^{l} w_i \geq \alpha \right. \right\}
\f]
